particles that are just the right size to allow blue light to get through the thin air more efficiently than it would on a planet like Earth  However  the light only stays near the area where the Sun is located in the sky  so the rest of the sky appears yellowish orange  just like it does during the day  Combine that with the fact that the Sun only appears to be about half as big as it does on Earth  and you get an almost eerie scene  This makes a Martian twilight even MORE beautiful  but it s not all just for looks   amp x B Martian sunsets have quite a bit of scientific value as well  Images taken from NASA s Curiosity and Opportunity rovers have allowed scientists to use the blue glow of Martian sunsets to determine just how high into the atmosphere the fine dust particles go  Other discoveries have also shown that the Sun s glow can still be visible for a few hours after sunset  similar to a phenomenon that occurs on Earth in areas where a volcano has recently erupted   amp x B As for sunrises on Mars  they make the Red Planet s familiar color  caused by iron oxide  also known as rust  pop even more  All in all  Mars is a beautiful planet  and we need to get there
